    96 				                    ;(W) Wait for horizontal synchronization. Allows the OS to
    97 				                    ;synchronize the vertical TV display by causing the 6502 to halt
    98 				                    ;and restart seven machine cycles before the beginning of the
    99 				                    ;next TV line. It is used to synchronize the VBI's or DLI's with the
   100 				                    ;screen display.
   101 				                    ;To see the effect of the WSYNC register, type in the second
